Communicated by:
HealthMap Alerts via ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The current outbreak of _Plasmodium falciparum_ malaria in Jamaica
started in 2006 and was the 1st autochthonous malaria in Jamaica
since 1966. _Anopheles albimanus_ is the most important malaria
vector in Jamaica as in Central America and is exophagic and
exophilic (out door biting and out door resting). Spraying therefore
has to cover natural vegetation, which is difficult especially as the
_A. albimanus_ has preferences for high resting places. Further
information on the situation and the control program would be
appreciated. - Mod.EP]

More information on the findings of an investigation, including
speciation of the organism involved, would be appreciated. - Mod.MPP]

[A map of Jamaica is available at
<http://mapsof.net/Jamaica/static-maps/gif/map-of-jamaica>.
Caymanas in St. Catherine Parish, south east Jamaica, can be located
via the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at <http://healthmap.org/r/006D>.

A photograph of _A. albimanus_ is available at
<http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Anopheles_albimanus_mosquito.jpg>.
- CopyEd.MJ]
